comments.body:
Here my tests (`0` coming for `ndigits <= -5`).  As expected, slowdown for small `abs(ndigits)` is noticeable (patch 1).

| Benchmark          | ref     | patch                | patch2               |
|--------------------|:-------:|:--------------------:|:--------------------:|
| round(17000, -1)   | 508 ns  | 647 ns: 1.27x slower | 481 ns: 1.06x faster |
| round(17000, -2)   | 484 ns  | 618 ns: 1.28x slower | 471 ns: 1.03x faster |
| round(17000, -3)   | 587 ns  | 672 ns: 1.14x slower | 549 ns: 1.07x faster |
| round(17000, -4)   | 682 ns  | 784 ns: 1.15x slower | 673 ns: 1.01x faster |
| round(17000, -5)   | 561 ns  | 696 ns: 1.24x slower | 549 ns: 1.02x faster |
| round(17000, -6)   | 577 ns  | 312 ns: 1.85x faster | 555 ns: 1.04x faster |
| round(17000, -7)   | 613 ns  | 313 ns: 1.96x faster | 584 ns: 1.05x faster |
| round(17000, -8)   | 562 ns  | 312 ns: 1.80x faster | not significant      |
| round(17000, -9)   | 612 ns  | 312 ns: 1.96x faster | 595 ns: 1.03x faster |
| round(17000, -10)  | 653 ns  | 311 ns: 2.10x faster | 658 ns: 1.01x slower |
| round(17000, -20)  | 958 ns  | 311 ns: 3.08x faster | 197 ns: 4.87x faster |
| round(17000, -50)  | 1.45 us | 311 ns: 4.66x faster | 197 ns: 7.37x faster |
| round(17000, -100) | 1.97 us | 311 ns: 6.33x faster | 197 ns: 9.99x faster |
| Geometric mean     | (ref)   | 1.69x faster         | 1.61x faster         |

We try different cutoff tests.  First version - close to the original proposal (almost literally it's `math.log10(self)`, which we can simplify further - `_PyLong_Frexp()` is an important part here), second - seems cheaper, but will be successful only for much bigger `abs(ndigits)`.  I appreciate if someone repeat tests on less noisy system.

<details>

<summary>Patch and benchmark code.</summary>

Patch 1:
```diff
diff --git a/Objects/longobject.c b/Objects/longobject.c
index 692312c1ad..36f9d95b9c 100644
--- a/Objects/longobject.c
+++ b/Objects/longobject.c
@@ -6212,6 +6212,21 @@ int___round___impl(PyObject *self, PyObject *o_ndigits)
         return long_long(self);
     }

+    int64_t n, e;
+
+    if (PyLong_AsInt64(ndigits, &n) < 0) {
+        Py_DECREF(ndigits);
+        return NULL;
+    }
+    n = -n;
+
+    double x = _PyLong_Frexp((PyLongObject *)self, &e);
+
+    if ((int64_t)(log10(x) + 0.3010299956639812*e) < n - 1) {
+        Py_DECREF(ndigits);
+        return _PyLong_GetZero();
+    }
+
     /* result = self - divmod_near(self, 10 ** -ndigits)[1] */
     PyObject *temp = (PyObject*)long_neg((PyLongObject*)ndigits);
     Py_SETREF(ndigits, temp);
```

Patch 2:
```diff
diff --git a/Objects/longobject.c b/Objects/longobject.c
index 692312c1ad..6ca54cbb55 100644
--- a/Objects/longobject.c
+++ b/Objects/longobject.c
@@ -6212,6 +6212,21 @@ int___round___impl(PyObject *self, PyObject *o_ndigits)
         return long_long(self);
     }

+    int64_t n;
+
+    if (PyLong_AsInt64(ndigits, &n) < 0) {
+        Py_DECREF(ndigits);
+        return NULL;
+    }
+    n = -n;
+
+    int64_t nbits = _PyLong_NumBits(self) + 1;
+
+    if (nbits + 1 < n) {
+        Py_DECREF(ndigits);
+        return _PyLong_GetZero();
+    }
+
     /* result = self - divmod_near(self, 10 ** -ndigits)[1] */
     PyObject *temp = (PyObject*)long_neg((PyLongObject*)ndigits);
     Py_SETREF(ndigits, temp);
```

```py
# bench.py
import pyperf
runner = pyperf.Runner()
d = 17000
for n in list(range(1, 11)) + [20, 50, 100]:
    n = -n
    s = f"round({d}, {n})"
    runner.bench_func(s, round, d, n)
```

</details>

CC @tim-one
